03/06/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police forces from Croatia, Slovenia, Serbia, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Macedonia have carried out a joint operation to bust a crime ring that was smuggling illegal immigrants to the EU, regional police directors stated at a press conference in Belgrade on Friday (June 1st) . Some 77 members of the group were arrested -- 11 in Serbia, 16 in Croatia, 19 in Macedonia, ten in BiH and 21 in Slovenia. Immigrants were reportedly paying the smugglers around 2,000-3,000 euros for the trip. (Hina, Makfax, Beta. B 92 - 01/06/07) 
